This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the study of adversarial training, which is a popular technique in machine learning for improving the robustness of models against adversarial attacks. Additionally, the paper also discusses the role of network capacity, which is a key aspect of deep learning models. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses the performance of models on vision tasks and the use of batch normalization, which is a common technique in computer vision. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the use of machine learning techniques for improving model robustness. The paper also involves computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it discusses the issue of adversarial attacks and the need for defenses against them. Finally, the paper also involves neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it discusses the use of deep neural networks for adversarial training.
